entry.tran: 无法决定的；未作出决定的；犹豫不决的
entry.def: If someone is undecided, they cannot decide about something or have not yet decided about it.

example.ex: After university she was still undecided as to what career she wanted to pursue...
example.tran: 大学毕业后她仍决定不下来要从事什么职业。

example.ex: He says he's counting on undecided voters to help him win next week's election.
example.tran: 他说他寄希望于尚未作出决定的选民帮他赢得下周的选举。

means.word_mean: 1. not brought to a conclusion; subject to further thought;

sentences.sentence: "our position on this bill is still undecided"
"some who had been on the fence came out in favor of the plan"
"too many voters still declare they are undecided"

means.word_mean: 3. not yet having made a commitment;
